questionResults.questionText: Tell me about the McDonald's project
questionResults.response:
Denys Honcharenko worked on the McDonald's Global App (GMAL) as a Lead Android Engineer and KMM Developer from August 2021 to October 2022. The app is the world's most downloaded food and beverage app, serving over 100 million users across 60+ countries. Denys was responsible for working on the MDS (Delivery) and Payments feature streams, implementing KMP shared libraries for both Android and iOS. He also designed the architecture for 20+ payment providers and delivery integrations.

Some notable achievements in this project include leading the ViewBinding migration using IntelliJ SSR tooling, creating the Android Talks initiative, and establishing the gmal-lite-rc Slack channel for improved release processes. The project showcases Denys' expertise in Kotlin, Kotlin Multiplatform (KMM), Jetpack Compose, and Coroutines.

The McDonald's Global App project demonstrates Denys' ability to work on large-scale, complex applications with multiple payment providers and delivery integrations. It also highlights his leadership skills, as he created initiatives to improve the development process and led the migration to new technologies.
